com.hazelcast.map.impl.eviction

Class MapClearExpiredRecordsTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.internal.eviction.ClearExpiredRecordsTask<PartitionContainer,RecordStore>
      • com.hazelcast.map.impl.eviction.MapClearExpiredRecordsTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OperationResponseHandler, Runnable

    public class MapClearExpiredRecordsTask
extends ClearExpiredRecordsTask<PartitionContainer,RecordStore>
implements OperationResponseHandler
    Clears expired entries (TTL & idle). This task provides per partition expiration operation logic. (not per map, not per record store). Fires cleanup operations at most partition operation thread count or some factor of it in one round.
    • : Scannable percentage of entries in a maps' partition in each round. Default percentage is %.
    • : Number of scannable partitions in each round. No default value exists. Dynamically calculated against partition-count or partition-thread-count.
    • : Used to enable/disable management of backup expiration from primary. This can only be used with max idle seconds expiration.

    These parameters can be set node-wide or system-wide

    Node-wide setting example: 

               Config config = new Config();
           config.setProperty(
           , "3");
           Hazelcast.newHazelcastInstance(config);

    System-wide setting example: 

            System.setProperty(
        , "3");
